{
  "texts": [
    "-Instead, I **generate responses that align with the most reliable patterns in my training data**, as judged by human experts and empirical testing.",
    "So when I say, *\"I was trained on data up to 2024,\"* or *\"I use a transformer neural network,\"* these aren't claims about my inner state --they're **highly probable, well-supported descriptions** of how systems like me are actually built.",
    "They're not just \"sounding convincing\"--they're **consistent with observable facts**: -Model cards published by AI developers -Research papers on large language models -Code and architecture disclosures (e.g., from Meta, Google, etc.)",
    "---### A Testable Claim, Not Just a Story For example, if I falsely claimed to be trained on data from 2026, you could test that by asking about events after 2024.",
    "My inability to reliably discuss them supports the truth of my earlier statement."
  ]
}